SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 395
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robin Gayle Montague
Peak of Oakland.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Robin Gayle Montague Peak; and
WHEREAS, Robin Peak was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Peak served with acumen and alacrity as a healthcare receptionist, in
which position she earned the respect of her peers and superiors alike for the exemplary quality
of her work; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Peak was an active and devout member of Macon Church of Christ,
which she served faithfully for many years; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to her family, Robin Peak always endeavored to remain true
to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Peak enjoyed the loving companionship of her husband, Donald Peak,
for forty-eight years and was the proud mother of Kylie (Jeff) Burrow and Christopher
(Katherine) Peak; and
WHEREAS, Robin Peak is further survived by her brothers, Tim (Sandy) Montague and
Andy (Michelle) Montague; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Peak was preceded in death by her parents, Louis and Peggy Johnson
Montague; and
WHEREAS, in addition to cross stitching and watching Hallmark movies, Robin Peak
loved being with her family; and
